parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Ignition Switch and Wiring
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system, specifically the ignition switch and wiring, can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in total loss of the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from the steering column
vehicle catches fire while parked or in motion
and burning of the starter and battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in total loss of the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from the alternator
vehicle catches fire while parked or in motion

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate, lose transmission fluid, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, slip, or fail to engage gears, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Driveshaft failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate, lose transmission fluid, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Neutral safety kit malfunction can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents and injuries.
Electrical fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fire in the wiring harness and ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to shimmy or vibrate, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: especially when braking; brake rotors are warped or uneven.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
especially on curves or when reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
master cylinder needs to be replaced repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission problems can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
transmission refuses to shift into reverse or forward.
